<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/kha_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Tournament Reports</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Tournament Reports</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/swccg/treports/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/treports/treports.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/treports/treports.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/kha_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Don&#39;t Walk, Run! Singapore 5/4/2002<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(5.00)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=10714'>TM ""Bu Qingyun"" Lee</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=10714&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> May 5, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> _A FIRST ONE FOR ME_<br>
Hi y&#39;all, due to my work commitments and all, no chance to post any tourney reports or stuff since joining Decktech. Anyway, David F has been pretty prolific churning out reports for us, earning his keep as Singapore&#8217;s #1 LOTR player. A warning for those who can&#8217;t stand boring stuff, this is a pretty long report too &#8230; so go easy on me, &#8216;kay? Thanks!<br>
<br>
Going into this week&#39;s tourney as the 2nd ranked player in the city of Singapore (current world rank: 232), I kinda felt that there was a giant bullseye sitting on my head. I would have been glad just to get off with a 3-1 this time round, as there were more players than usual due to the school holidays just starting. Quite a few top 10 players were around, as well as various notorious personalities/decks ... Frankie, the _former_ Singapore #1 came late. We were kinda eager to see if he would make a comeback. Davd Feng, with his much vaunted Men and Short Men deck gave the tourney a miss because he had to go for some Youth association thingy - though he lent his deck to his friend Lan, also another contender. Mun Kit, with his 4 ARV 4 PATHs deck ... Leck Khoon with his 7-archery per turn shoulderfire (modified to Goblin/Armories/Relics/Weapons/Cave Troll swarm though...i wonder if it cost him).    <br>
<br>
 I had a bad feeling before it even started ... was talking metagame with my adopted master Adrian (Tan: there are many Adrians here). Master seemed to be in favor of uruk weenies ... 3 costers for the potential gang-clober at sites 4-5-7-8-9, dropping his old concept of 4 parties and 4 troops to suck up sniper-fire from ranger/elf. I thought that was cool, but i decided to stick with what he had taught me (which had won me quite a few games) initially: 4 Troops 4 Parties 4 Lieutenants and spiced with wariness to punish stealth-reliant decks. I felt Fighters were kinda iffy because Aragorn with sword or Boromir with Blade or Gandalf or even Arwen with Gwem could cut them down, not to mention FOTSF. The strategy pulled me through the last two tourneys because I was able to push wariness through to stop hobbit hospitals from running (double warinessed to overwhelm Sam, breaking the Promise and putting 2 wounds on Frodo at the Bridge) plus during the last tourney, I won 3 out of 4 games by canceling stealths.  <br>
<br>
  Fearing a bad match-up against Uruks or mirror, I dropped Rumil for an extra hobbit pump card while retaining Orophin to snipe down a 2-vitality uruk and double-move, confident that my deck could take any moria/sauron deck with its existing powers ... well, maybe too much thinking and talking screws you (so sorry for the long intro, guys!!!) as we shall see ....    <br>
  <br>
<br>
 Myself:		TM Lee<br>
 9 Walkers/Isengard Skirmish Beatdown <br>
 Bearer:		Frodo, OBH<br>
           		TOR, TRR<br>
<br>
 Starting:	Legolas, POM<br>
          	Gimli, SOG<br>
 <br>
 Game 1<br>
 Vs. Sam Goh  <br>
 Hobbit Hospital/ Sauron Hates Archery<br>
 Start: Frodo OBH/Sam SOH/Merry FTS/Pippin HOSE<br>
 <br>
 Haven&#39;t seen Sam in the last few tourneys ... he no longer started his Legolas, Greenleaf and Son of Gloin combo. Ah, a new deck. He was also walking around asking for a Hobbiton Party field before the games started ... so Bilbo, Well-Spoken no doubt ... had heard all the buzz about Consorting the past week ... Bids 5. Ooh, can&#39;t top that ... removes 3+1 with Sam and Pippin. He starts off fine and plays a bunch of allies. Darn ... Rosie I think, and removes last burden. However, he gives a bit too much twilight and faces two uruks at site 2. No double-move for him.<br>
<br>
My turn ... drop Gandalf. I walk, and he plays  Orc Bowmen and a power 6 tracker. Tracker gets shot by legolas once, and clobbered by FOTSF. I give 4 twilight, nuff for another tracker and he plays watching eye. Next site, Frodo&#39;s bedroom. Ok, more draw for him. <br>
<br>
My Uruks keep him to one site at a time from then on, and I manage to pull off two Sleep, Caradhases which pretty much killed off his deck. Fearing a series of double-walks from his buff hobbit hospital, I charge headlong into site 9 myself, losing Arwen to a Hate on the way, but he gets screwed at site 8, pulling no orcs and without the 5 spotted orcs (have they been breeding with leopards?!) at the shores, I zoom into Emyn Muil with the map, not giving him Tol Brandir.  <br>
<br>
FW +3/+3<br>
<br>
Game 2<br>
Vs.  Yunn Shing (sorry if I didn&#8217;t spell it right)<br>
The Advanced Dungeons and Dragons Fellowship/ Moria Swarm<br>
Start: Legolas GL, Arwen DOE<br>
 <br>
	Never saw this guy before. You never know with unknown players, they might spring some weird stuff on you. But I relaxed a little when I saw his 80+ card deck &#8230;ahhh, Moria! He goes first but I get a good Uruk hand and manage to stop him.  My turn, I manage a just-in-time Gandalf and Dreary. He plays the usual armories and swarms stuff. I walk, and smack an armory so that my critical 1-point archery against the Moria goblins gets thru. Power 5 goblins against Legolas, &#8230; Keyward with scimitar? exert gimli twice with secret fire &#8230; it was already wounded by archery &#8230; dope!, and Power 8 scavenger  meets gandalf. I reach sanctuary. To add to his trouble, I draw Sting and keep the twilight for site 4 low. He is pressed to keep up, but due to Hollin and the Bridge, I make site 6 first. A sleep Caradhras along the way helps, as do Stealths at the bridge to cancel rare Balrog.   <br>
<br>
	Looking back at the monsters behind me(and I don&#8217;t mean the Moria punks), I&#8217;m glad I ran! By site 6 his fellowship looked like a broken AD&D party &#8230;Arwen with sword and bow, Boromir with blade and armor, Aragorn with bow/sword/armor, Legolas with Tale and Gandalf with staff?!?! What the &#8230; I was playing 3 cost uruks and skirmish events just to clear my hand. During the last leg, I dropped 3 uruks for Ottar to get fellowship cards, and exhausted Frodo so as not to give him any extra twilight. Shores at 8 but he has no more conditions and only a few minions in hand, and again, Discovery Channel fails to find the 5 mysterious spotted orcs.  I cruised into site 9 with a stealth, disquiet of our people in hand and about 7 companions including a 3 &#8211;vitality aragorn and gimli. Someone watching commented the match looked like a gosh darnit marathon and his guys couldn&#8217;t keep up because of their armor and toys&#8230;.!?! <br>
<br>
FW +3/+6<br>
<br>
Game 3<br>
Vs. Woon How <br>
Another Advanced Dungeons and Dragons Fellowship (ok, ok&#8230;Ranger-Elf!)/ Moria Swarm<br>
Start: Sam, Arwen DOE (I think &#8230;or it was Arwen +Legolas if not Sam)<br>
<br>
	I knew Woon How plays Nazgul and I was hoping for critical doubles against him. He bids 3 to start, and since I don&#8217;t have many ways to remove burdens I never bid more than 1 or 2. Ok, nevermind,  I draw my opening hand. What the &#8230; 5 fellowship cards &#8230; including 2 A Wizard is Never Late, plus:  Savagery, Spies of Saruman and Bred for Battle?!?  I try and imagine I am playing poker. I&#8217;ve got 1 pairs. Whats your last card? Grrr.  He calls out &#8220;Sting for 1 &#8230; Exert to &#8230; &#8221; Sheeeeit!!! To be fair, he was nice about it and did not say anything funny but I was hoping as a last resort he would laugh himself into a coma or something. I reconcile my hand. I draw into and play an Uruk Lieutenant at site 3 but he guns it down, not even giving me the chance to cycle the skirmish events from my hand. Very smart. But very evil &#8230; why choke someone already hand-screwed?! (sob) I play my gandalf and my ottar. At great cost, I double into site 3, though he already has Toldea out. Make my first mistake. Hoping to draw into Elrond, I did not sacrifice Ottar to a fierce skirmish, letting Legolas POM die (anyone figure out why yet, besides the Elrond?) and Boromir dies at the start of next turn having 2 wounds and a tip on him.  I&#8217;m cool. Good playing should get me through. I double into site 5, despite a witch king with pale blade making strange gestures at me in Hollin. He drops a Toldea again. Its really the Disquiet of Our People, and Gimli dies bravely. I stealth away the Witch King and Gandalf who was breathed somewhere along the way is forced to cancel a fierce skirmish because of a breath and tip on the board. My turn, I make a critical mistake. I drop 4 uruks and hoping to overwhelm Frodo I breed a power 9 warrior for battle, because Merry was assigned. He PATHs out. I should have dropped the +3 on someone else and killed a 2-wounded Aragorn, but noooo &#8230;I had to be cool and do the funky shimmer and try to win the game. <br>
<br>
	My turn at site 5. I drop arwen and only have 3 jokers with me. Gandalf and Frodo. We meet another nazgul at site 6. I&#8217;m forced to block with frodo. He gives frodo the breath. Very good. I was hoping for the tip too (who cares if I added 1 burden every turn, I was going to run!)&#8230; but I had no more boosters to take the second skirmish with him. I take a wound, wary of Return To Its Master (though to be (un)fair, Benjamen standing nearby made me think of it with his comments) and anyway it was Sanctuary naptime. He would have piled both on Arwen if I had blocked with her first. <br>
  <br>
   So Arwen bites the tip and 1 wound. That&#8217;s good playing. Next turn I heal her, take 1 and move again. She gets boffed twice by an Ulaire-Somebody and I&#8217;m forced to stop, also because my hand is full of shadow. He reaches a forest sanctuary by mapping and meets Lurtz and another uruk &#8230; ARV &#8230;shoots both down. (Oh hell, despite the bridge decision I would have been screwed ANYWAY &#8230; Arwen is a ranger and Legolas woulda shot them all so that was actually a meta-strategic move at the bridge? Too much thinking only &#8230;.) I only manage one other uruk next site, and its no use, he double-hops to 7. I&#8217;m at 7. I draw a glamdring, 1 servant and  2 stealths. No Filbert in sight, and bounder only. I do not want to play glamdring because that would give him enough twilight for two 5 cost nazgul. (6+2+2) He plays only Toldea, with a nazgul sword. Bad news. Gandalf is only 7, and though he has staff and 3 wounds, Toldea is 14 (overwhelm!). First time round I am forced to bounder and stealth. Second time,  bounder is exhausted and I can&#8217;t do jack. I am forced to serve Toldea some secret fire (sounds like I&#8217;m farting into his hood or something) to save gandalf. I think hard. No filbert. Exhausted bounder. 1 stealth in hand. It is mathematically impossible to survive a fierce skirmish, for my beautiful Sting had faded away at site 4 &#8230; Frodo&#8217;s 4+2 equals 6 only, and Gandalf would be overwhelmed immediately. I burn the last stealth to clear my hand. Frodo hides in a corner as Gandalf shows his backside defiantly to Toldea &#8230; <br>
<br>
	Will there be hope? He has 5 companions and I hold one savagery before reconciling. No chance in hell. I get my face rubbed into the dirt. First he plays an extra companion. Then he maps for the Summit and my Emyn Muil as well as any chance of winning goes. I am only able to muster 3 minions. Final hand &#8230; 1 uruk Lieut, 1 troop, 1 warrior, 1 bred, 2 savagery and 1 fellowship card. He shoots down the warrior and the rest is moot ... <br>
<br>
	Funniest part of the game was when he did not hear me say &#8220;I stop moving at site 8&#8221; and he played an Enquea onto the table. Oooh boy. I was dead any way you look at it &#8230; When you&#8217;re screwed, you&#8217;re screwed from beginning to end &#8230; and it was just beginning.<br>
<br>
FL +1/+7<br>
<br>
Game 4  <br>
Vs. Evan<br>
Hobtookoke with Gimli&#8217;s Help / Moria  <br>
Starts:	Gimli, DOTMR (???)<br>
	Sam, SOH	<br>
<br>
	Smelt trouble from the start. Funky decks are a pain. He&#8217;s playing Bilbo, WSGH with multiple consortings to clear twilight, along with Deft Movements to double run, and an assload of stealths and intuitions. I manage to stop him from doubling early. His Moria shadowship eats a double sleep Cardhras and I feed Arwen to a Cave Troll I think. For my shadow, I manage to Sarumans Power away 1 Talent for Not Being Seen, 1 Promise and 1 O Elbereth. He has to keep up and doubles into site 5, after consorting away one twilight during his fellowship and playing a Deft Movements &#8230; what the?! Gimli &#8211;2 Deft &#8211;2 &#8230;2 twilight from the bridge and 3 companions &#8230; 6 total?!? I look at my hand &#8230; 1 troop, 1 raiding party, 1 warrior &#8230; @#$%^! But, 1 wariness. So he takes Frodo on the Troop and I boost it to 13 with an ambition and a savagery. He stealths frodo but I cancel it with wariness.<br>
<br>
	Now this is the funny thing about tournament reports. Theres a certain amount of biasedness in any reporting, but as Evan himself has said, we don&#8217;t really go by the book all the time and we let people take back some moves if everybody&#8217;s cool with it. Heres my scoop and this is pretty true, too: He didn&#8217;t PATHS 3 times after seeing me exert the troop. I had already exerted it. Frodo was in the dead pile and the ring was on Sam. Seeing as how it was not a game-ending critical mistake, I let him &#8220;resurrect&#8221; Frodo and blow the 3 PATHs to kill the troop, being the nice guy that I am.<br>
<br>
	That cost me the game, as well as my stopping at the sanctuary at 6 (Why did I do that? I didn&#39;t expect him to double _double_...arrrgghhh) Fool that I was, Frodo was the lynchpin of the deck! He doubled TWICE &#8230; from 5 to 7 to 9! At 6 he played a double Deft during regroup to drain almost all the twilight (- 4 per site?! Wtf?!?) along with a little hanky-panky with wizardly types. From 7 crashing into 9, he naturally still gave enough for Lurtz and 3 Uruks &#8230;a scout, a raid party and a warrior. But although its Emyn Muil, I think hard. He probably has a fourth PATHS but Sam is strength 3 (sword) +1 (rosie) +1promise + 2 (There and back) = 7 and Frodo is .... obscene ... beyond the height of Lurtzes?!! ... <br>
4+2sting+2there and back+1 promise+3 stone trolls?!? With 2 bounders in play, it would have taken 36 to overwhelm him! I had no choice but to fierce all the minions and hope he wasn&#8217;t carrying PATHs. Now it turns out it was a mathematical impossibility because he had 2 more stealths in hand. And I realized TO MY ABSOLUTE HORROR that mithril coat negates all damage bonuses &#8230; 3 uruks on frodo?! Lose, take 4 wounds, right?<br>
Nope &#8230; take only 1. 9+13+9+7+2 savagery = 41&#8230; for the fierce skirmish  if Sam died (he took 2 wounds from Lurtz and he already had 2 and so Sam died)<br>
12+4 for two stealths = 16 x 3 = 48     <br>
No Chance&#8230; no chance in hell &#8230;. :P        <br>
Anyway, he drops his last PATHS to kill everything on Frodo except the raiding party and took 1 more wound from Lurtz. Sighhh&#8230;<br>
<br>
I cracked open my booster to see a Caradhras has not forgiven us. As I flip the rare, I see a common frodo looking depressed. I stick my tongue out at him too, but as my hand shifts slightly, he gleams in the twilight of the Comicsmart fluorescent lamps. A foil Son of Drogo!  Ah well &#8230; my reward for being nice after all.  <br>
 <br>
FINALS<br>
At the finalists table, they took quite some time to finish. I saw Leck Khoon playing a Moria/Shoulderfire variant from his normal Nazgul. Why did he change it, I wonder? Nazgul are better for stopping buff fellowships from relentlessly charging.  Moria orcs get bullied a lot. On the other hand, Chin Seng played twilight nazgul corruption with swords and toldeas. <br>
<br>
Toldea went after Leck Khoon&#8217;s Boromir and killed him (he had lost Aragorn already) and a Twilight Witch King with sword poked Arwen to death at site 8 even after getting ARV&#8217;ed.  Leck Khoons only hope for survival was ironically if Seng wanted to double into the last site with a bunch of moria flankers on the swarms and a relics in play &#8230; errr&#8230;! But hey, who would not have not doubled either, because how often you get a Frodo alone to torment! Last site was Emyn Muil and down came a Twilight Witchking with a Nazgul Sword?! Fierce, and there were like 6-7 burdens &#8230; a His Terrible Servants in play and so no chance in hell (:P) of a 3 PATHS or whatever because 1 more twilight left &#8230;erm 4 PATHS? That would mean 10 burdens &#8230;<br>
Dang ..that&#8217;s like 16 strength fierce damage +1 take 4 wounds and exert to wound 2 times 2 for 4 more wounds?!  <br>
When you gotta go, you gotta go...<br>
<br>
Props:<br>
Chin Seng, for winning with an ultra funky twilight corruption deck <br>
(Hey, anyone wanna buy my foil wraith worlds? Please???)<br>
Moria, for having lots of 5 strength and 1 vitality minions.<br>
Foil Son of Drogo<br>
Me being nice? <br>
<br>
Slops:<br>
Drawing 3 conditions/events and no minions for a first hand, and going 2ND<br>
Me being nice? <br>
